    <briefdescription>
<para>No-op mutex backend <ndash/> all operations compile to nothing. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This is the default backend when no RTOS or threading support is configured. Handle types are minimal (uint8_t) so mutex members occupy a single byte. Every operation is constexpr / inline and produces no machine code.</para>
<para>This struct also serves as the DOCUMENTATION of the backend contract: any concrete backend must provide the exact same set of static methods with compatible signatures. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
